Whipped cream (optional) Chocolate sauce (optional)
and cherries (optional). Step 1. Line a baking

00:00:42.960 --> 00:00:47.870
sheet with parchment paper. Step 2. Scoop
eight balls of vanilla ice cream onto the

00:00:47.870 --> 00:00:54.190
lined baking sheet and put it in the freezer
for an hour, until the ice cream is solid.

00:00:54.190 --> 00:00:59.250
Step 3. Whip the egg whites in a medium bowl
until they are foamy. Put the crushed cereal

00:00:59.250 --> 00:01:04.619
in another bowl. Use cookie crumbs, coconut
flakes, or chopped walnuts instead of or in

00:01:04.619 --> 00:01:09.920
addition the cereals. Step 4. Remove the ice
cream from the freezer and roll each ball

00:01:09.920 --> 00:01:13.829
in the egg whites, then in the cereal, and
then place them back on the baking sheet.

00:01:13.829 --> 00:01:18.100
Make your fried ice cream extra crispy by
dipping each ice cream ball in the eggs and

00:01:18.100 --> 00:01:23.880
cereal a second time. Step 5. Return the baking
sheet to the freezer for at least three more

00:01:23.880 --> 00:01:29.719
hours, until the balls are frozen. Step 6.
Add 4 inches vegetable oil to a Dutch oven

00:01:29.719 --> 00:01:36.090
or large pot and heat it to 375 degrees. Add
Â¼ teaspoon of salt to the oil just before

00:01:36.090 --> 00:01:41.429
frying to keep it from splattering. Step 7.
Fry the frozen ice cream balls until they're

00:01:41.429 --> 00:01:47.020
golden brown, about 1 minute. Then place them
in dessert dishes and garnish them with cinnamon,

00:01:47.020 --> 00:01:53.039
honey, whipped cream, chocolate sauce, and
